article_text:
Hillary Clinton’s critics were expecting a puffball interview, especially after the Weekly Standard’s Daniel Halper pointed out that the questioner, Brianna Keilar, recently attended the wedding of Mrs. Clinton’s “director of grassroots engagement” to an erstwhile staffer for the Ready for Hillary Super PAC. Keilar’s interview was not as bad as all that, though she left some important questions unasked and missed some opportunities for tough follow-ups.

There were revealing moments. Asked about the Bernie Sanders boomlet,...
